@node Basics "Basics about VSConv"
@prev Copyright
@next Compatibility

@{u}WHAT DOES IT DO?@{uu}

This program is a small utility to convert older VoiceShell and VCLI
data files to a newer format. It allows you to easily switch from one
version of @{b}VoiceShell@{ub} to another or from Richard Horne's VCLI 7.0 to
@{b}VoiceShell@{ub} (VCLI will not be updated anymore).
@endnode

@node Compatibility "What is VSConv compatible with?"
@prev Basics
@next CLIStart

@{u}COMPATIBILITY@{uu}

@{b}VSConv@{ub} will currently convert data files for @{b}VoiceShell@{ub} 1.07 upto
1.24 into the format @{b}VoiceShell@{ub} 1.25 and up understand. @{b}VSConv@{ub}
also converts VCLI 7.0 files.
@endnode

@node CLIStart "Starting VSConv from a CLI/Shell"
@prev Compatibility
@next Examples

@{u}STARTING FROM CLI/SHELL@{uu}

You can start the program only from a CLI/SHELL/etc.

To run the program, enter the following into your CLI/SHELL/etc.

	1> VSConv FROM/A,PREFS,TO/A/K

	Where:  FROM is the source file, i.e. the file to convert.

		PREFS allows you to specify the preferences file for
		@{b}VoiceShell@{ub}. If not given, current defaults will be
		written.

		TO is the filename of the converted file. The keyword 'TO'
		must be given!
@endnode

@node Examples "Examples"
@prev CLIStart
@next Problems

@{u}EXAMPLES@{uu}

	1> VSConv FROM S:VoiceShell.OLD TO RAM:MyProject.VS


	1> VSConv FROM S:VoiceShell.DAT PREFS ENVARC:VoiceShell.PREFS
	   TO RAM:MyProject.VS


	1> VSConv FROM S:VCLI.commands TO S:VoiceShell.VS
@endnode

@node Problems "Possible problems that You might encounter"
@prev Examples
@next Errors

@{u}PROBLEMS@{uu}

@{b}VSConv@{ub} looks at the file size to identify @{b}VoiceShell@{ub}
data files and if it doesn't match it tries to find a known header for VCLI
data files. If you specify a file that has the same length that a @{b}VoiceShell@{ub}
data file has, but isn't one, @{b}VSConv@{ub} will still try to convert it!
You might encounter problems with data files between version 1.12 - 1.18.
@endnode

@node Errors "Error messages displayed by VSConv"
@prev Problems
@next Bugs

@{u}ERROR MESSAGES@{uu}

The @{b}VSConv@{ub} program will display necessary error messages. If a window
can't be opened, the user will be informed. I HATE PROGRAMS THAT DON'T TELL
WHAT-THE-HELL IS GOING ON! That clear? If @{b}VSConv@{ub} doesn't give any 
output something has gone terribly wrong.

@{b}NOTE!@{ub} Kickstart versions under 39 have a bug in the
dos.library/Seek() routine and it doesn't give the correct error code. This
may cause @{b}VSConv@{ub} to not give an error code if a seek error
happens.
@endnode

@node Bugs "Known bugs"
@prev Errors
@next Versions

@{u}BUGS@{uu}

No known bugs at the moment. @{b}VSConv@{ub} might have some since this is
a rather quick hack. Especially converting versions between 1.12 - 1.18
might cause problems. Be warned!
@endnode

